history.text: Hi, there!  Did you see Batman Begins?
Yes i did, did you?
Yes! I went with my husband. He loves comic book stuff -- I typically don't, but I love Michael Caine. He always plays such unusual parts! What did you think?
i liked the dark tone of the movie
Oh, yes, it did have that, didn't it? Christopher Nolan gets pretty dark! Who was your favorite actor in it?
christian bale was my favorite actor
He's really good. My favorite comic book type movies (seen lots iwth hubby) are those where they tell the "becoming the hero" part -- the history, rather than just another adventure.
me too but i dont watch a lot of comic book movies
I only do when dragged, but I'm dragged a lot.......    I also love seeing Morgan Freeman. He makes it feel "like home," because I've seen so many movies with him in it.
yeah he is good too. i would like the comic movies more if they were so geared toward children
Well, hell, I'd develop a phobia if I were attacked by a swarm of bats, wouldn't you?
yes lol
not to mentioned watched my parents get murdered

I agree. Shocking! As a side note, my mother witnessed the murder of her godmother
!!!
dang thats crazy
Nice to be raised by the butler, though. Like being raised by a really nice older brother.
yeah i could get used to that

Same here. Parents can be a nuisance. Like the anti-revenge theme on the one hand, but glad someone got him (on the other)
!
i enjoyed the movie and the sequels
Yes. It was good. I love the name "League of Shadows." It's so immaterial.
i like the origin aspects
yeah it is cool
Same here. I like the part where he's in prison, too, but I have a fascination with institutions.
yeah they did a good job with the prison
scenes
Well, I love the fear inducing drug. Sounds like PCP!
i liked the ninja scenes on the mountain too
I don't love it as in take it myself, of course. No way!
I can't imagine how much it would cost to rebuild Wayne Manor after the fire....
im sure it wouldnt be a problem for him lol
I would find it very odd to encounter an individual who went around shouting "Scarcrow." For sure.
i agree
